dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Asif Ali b Shoaib Malik 59 (75b 5x4 2x6 117m) SR: 78.66

dismissalComment.html: high in the air and taken at deep midwicket. It's a good catch, this was really high and swerving to Asi Ali's left. He followed it and lunged low to his left to hold on. Masakadza was looking to swat Malik far over the leg side with a slog sweep but got it right off the toe end. A bad end to a good innings. He won't be happy in the manner it has come.

dismissalComment.html: Harakiri! Full on middle, and Fakhar defends with soft hands. The ball stays near Fakhar's toes, and off they go for a single. The bowler runs towards the ball, picks it up, and then breaks the stumps, but Imam's dive should save him. But oh wait, looks like Imam's bat is in the air. It's crossed the crease, but it hasn't been grounded at all. What a terrible way to get out. There's the breakthrough

commentPreTextItems.html: One run to win. Those who predicted a 37-over finish, all of you deserve a chocolate.

commentTextItems.html: short and wide down the leg side, and that's the end! Pakistan win by nine wickets.

commentPostTextItems.html: 4.05pm That's all from us at Bulawayo. Another dominating win for Pakistan. Surely they're favourites to go all the way and win 5-0, eh? To see if they actually can complete a washout in Zimbabwe, join us in a few days for the third ODI. Till then, on behalf of Varun Shetty, this is Sreshth Shah, saying khuda hafiz and good bye!
4pm Time for the presentation.

Sarfraz Ahmed, the winning captain: "Thanks to Allah. Shenwari bowled brilliantly, but Fakhar and Babar did the job for us. Usman's bowled really well after his injury. Took five wickets against Sri Lanka on a flat surface earlier. Getting better day by day. We are lacking a bit in the fielding, but otherwise we are doing very good. Chances of a couple of team shuffling, but first we want to win the series."

Fakhar Zaman, the Man of the Match: "If you are in form, and you are giving your 100%, then the runs will come. Trying my level best, and doing well. Should utilise your good form. Today I was trying to go till the end. Tried with Imam, he was unlucky (smiles) but I wanted to stay till the end. Batting was easy in both innings."

Hamilton Masakadza, the losing captain: "Tough day in the office. I got out the wrong time trying to up the game, but the target was never going to be enough. We're losing wickets at crucial times, and also not rotating the strike enough. They've played our spinners really well, and with such a score, it was always going to be difficult for our bowlers. Hopefully we can put up a better performance, and make the series competitive."
Aslam: "Don't read much in these wins. Should worry about M. Amir not getting a wicket. What he will do against teams like India, Aussies or SA. "
Ali Ahad: "Babar will score hundred in 3rd one day"
imran: ""what a pair fakhar and imam is proving to be in zimbabwe series. imam got 100 in first game and fakhar in 2nd .who will score his 2nd series hundred first. Fakhar or imam?""

3.52pm Another century from a Pakistan opener, another win for Pakistan. A drama-free second innings, barring Imam Ul Haq's run out, as the visitors go up 2-0. Fakhar shakes the hand of his opponents, as his highest ODI score ensured Pakistan romped home. The game, however, was set up by their bowlers, led by Usman Khan's four-wicket haul. The fact that Fakhar finished unbeaten would give him a whole lotta confidence. Stick around with us. We'll be back with the presentation party.
Khawaja: "Well technically game ended in 36th over ,coz no legal bowl of 37th over was bowler" -- you, sir, deserve a special prize.
Mian Kashif: "Zimbabwe Cricket board needs to think seriously about thier developed players,Zimbabwe is lot better than these performances. Pay them and get their services. Only way for Zimbawe."
Arsalan Iqtidar: "Fakhar Zaman needs just 273 runs in next 5 innings to become the fastest batsman to score 1000 ODI runs! "
Simon: "Ha ha, Boycott made 14 off 36 balls chasing that target of 46...would love to have seen it"
Muhammad Umair: "Averages of Pakistan top 3 batsman are over 50. very rare sight, might be the first time "

commentPreTextItems.html: That's his highest ODI score now.

commentTextItems.html: good length on leg, and fended back to the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: Hemant: "I can't wait for September to come, Asia Cup 2018 is going to be so exicting."

commentTextItems.html: good length outside off, and cut away to the point boundary. Makes some extra room, and sends this into the boundary. Scores tied
full on middle, and he sweeps this fine down the leg side! Placed to perfection, and deep midwicket just can't cut it off
good length outside leg, and Fakhar misses the cut shot. The ball goes under his bat, and then through the keeper's legs for a bye
full on off, and drilled down the ground to long off. A walking single

commentPostTextItems.html: Ibrahim: "Rohan almost jinxed fakhar"
Wasim Baig: "We love you too, Rohan - from all of Pakistan"

commentTextItems.html: full and wide outside off again, and Fakhar can't reach at this ball. It's inside the tramlines and the umpire says that's a legal ball. Over

commentPostTextItems.html: Syed Hasnain Bo: "I don't think Pakistan should test anything with fakhar before world Cup 2019. Because he will try to stay on pitch for test which will effect his natural game. "

commentPreTextItems.html: Abrar: "Shah could you get me me the list of highest win margin in 2nd inning in an ODI." -- The record is a 277 ball win. Here's the record list.

commentTextItems.html: length ball on middle, and going through to the keeper as Fakhar tries to ramp it over
back of a length on leg, and nudged off the back foot to the vacant fine-leg region
full and wide outside off. Saw Fakhar coming down the wicket, and delivers this slightly wider than usual. Fakhar properly deceived as the ball goes through to Murray, the keeper
good length on leg, and he taps this away to point. Wants a single, but Babar sends him back. One run-out is enough per game, reckons the Pakistan batsmen

commentPreTextItems.html: rohan: "Oh Boy ! Zaman is in red hot form (just had a look at his last 5 innings). I love Pakistan - With love from India "

commentTextItems.html: good length on leg, and he flicks it straight to short fine leg. Could've been a catch, but the fielder there drops it! Deceived by the slower ball and Fakhar scoops this by mistake. Tendai Chitara the guilty man
full on leg, and tapped to the vacant leg side region for a quick single

commentPostTextItems.html: Qasim: "I would disagree to Fakhar being given a chance in test cricket. We are gonna spoil his limited overs games like we did to Sharjeel"
hassan iqbal: "@"Omair Siddiqui, Fakhar surely can do a Jos Butler role for Pak in tests""

commentPreTextItems.html: Ali cheema : "Who is your man of the match? Fakhar or Shinwari? For me its Shinwari whose 4 wickets set up this easy chase for the batsmen " -- If I had a choice, I'd say Fakhar. Only reason was that two of Usman's wickets were tailenders

commentTextItems.html: good length outside off, and cut away
full on leg stump, and Fakhar taps this down the ground to long of. Dealing in singles now
full outside off, and he comes down the ground to drive to long off
aimed at his legs, and Fakhar - once again - flicks it off his pads to square leg
full outside off, and Fakhar connects with the big shot. Thumps a hard drive down the ground, but straight to wide long off

commentPostTextItems.html: mir Ali: "I was telling you that it will over until 37th over but my comment has been ignored. I'm saying it based on watching Pakistan cricket for almost 12 years."

dismissalComment.html: big appeal and it's given! Is he a little unlucky there? Shuffles across and looks to flick a length ball. He has broken the partnership.

dismissalText.commentary: Imam-ul-Haq run out (Muzarabani) 44 (51b 4x4 0x6 87m) SR: 86.27

dismissalComment.html: Harakiri! Full on middle, and Fakhar defends with soft hands. The ball stays near Fakhar's toes, and off they go for a single. The bowler runs towards the ball, picks it up, and then breaks the stumps, but Imam's dive should save him. But oh wait, looks like Imam's bat is in the air. It's crossed the crease, but it hasn't been grounded at all. What a terrible way to get out. There's the breakthrough
